    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-08T11:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-08T11:45:00-05:00" n="778"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2182: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-08T11:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1920—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 9—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Department’s May 4, 5 p.m. Am informed that only small band of Honduranean
                    bandits may be operating on the frontier. Am satisfied the President can arrange
                    matter with the Honduranean Minister here.</p>
                <p>The President suggested to Honduranean Minister that his Government grant general
                    amnesty to all exiles. This the Honduranean Minister is communicating to his
                    Govt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
